data.title: Gina Torres Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Gina Torres with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Majored in voice at New York City's prestigious Fiorello H

LaGuardia High School of Music & Art and the Performing Arts (aka "the Fame school")

Made TV debut on One Life to Live (the same soap in which Laurence Fishburne, whom she married in 2002, got his start)

Worked with Fishburne in The Matrix Reloaded, The Matrix: Revolutions and the 2006 political thriller Five Fingers

Won 2001 ALMA Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Syndicated Drama Series for Cleopatra 2525

Voice work has included the character Vixen on the Cartoon Network's Justice League Unlimited, Airachnid on Transformers: Prime and Niobe on the computer game The Matrix Online
